        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 2:19PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 219 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Emory Pass, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hillsboro and Portions of the Aldo Leopold Wilderness.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
